Its fun, but the game crashes alot. Needs to fix this issue.

- In-Office UI needs better controls for doors and vents, or possibly, just have the entire office showing instead of having the Scroll dynamic/Perspective object without the mouse that uses it best. Nothing like having your mask on while having Ballora at the open right door and not being able to scroll over to shut it in time (as opposed to fast-hitting D on the PC version). 

- Boxes up top for Power Gen/GMB/etc. are awfully small, and they also irritate Nightmarionne, which throws that dynamic even more out of balance. - Rockstar Foxy does a weird pop in and out (fattens then slims down when you click Mebird). 

- RWQFSFASXC appearing: shows doors and vents as closed, but they're not. Weird graphical glitch when RWQFSFASXC disappears. 

- Visiting Settings Menu resets all of your AI settings to 0. Annoying when you've taken forever to adjust what you want and then coming back to have to do it all over again. 

- Adjusting AI takes a painfully long time. Please add something to set things to 0, 5, 10, 20, OR make a slider object that allows for faster selection. 

- Old Man Consequences is way too active, and his tap needs more leniency for how much he lags out the game. El Chip, as well...too active, and no Enter shortcut to get rid of the ad. Were the random appearance proportions from PC taken out entirely? Withered Bonnie, Rockstar Bonnie, and Rockstar Freddy seem to be in the same camp...every :13 if the camera is up (instead of random-chance), and just about every camera flip, Rockstar Freddy wants 5 coins. 

- Nightmarionne is not nearly generous enough give you now have to click everything instead of hit the keyboard for most stuff. 

- Flashlight button needs more touch leniency. I can get away with this if I play w/ my S-Pen, but not everyone has an S-Pen. 

- Maybe have a different color for the borders on the No-Aspect-Stretch mode -- really hard to tell where the edge of the adjusted screen is when everything is the same color. 

- Fonts on the intro sound screen, etc. should probably be a bit bigger -- really miniscule on a phone. 

- Golden Freddy has magenta jaggies on the bottom of his jumpscare chin. 

- Challenges UI: Doesn't show which challenge is selected. No way to cancel out of dialog if you don't want to change challenge. Can click 'Go' while still selecting your Challenge. Have to select a different challenge and then the old challenge if you want to play the same challenge again after going to this menu.
